 data centre launched in China]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131245569.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/servers-in-the-ocean-worlds-first-offshore-underwater-ai-data-centre-launched-in-china/articleshow/131245569.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/servers-in-the-ocean-worlds-first-offshore-underwater-ai-data-centre-launched-in-china/articleshow/131245569.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T16:32:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131245658,imgsize-1415746.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists found fossil pollen that revealed a hidden Nile channel used to build the Great Pyramid]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131241650.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Ancient Egyptians ingeniously utilized a forgotten, high-volume Nile branch, the Khufu Branch, to transport massive pyramid stones. Scientific evidence reveals this 'water highway' flowed directly to Giza, proving they worked smarter, not harder. This natural waterway, sustained by a wetter climate, facilitated efficient logistics, solving the mystery of pyramid construction.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-found-fossil-pollen-that-revealed-a-hidden-nile-channel-used-to-build-the-great-pyramid/articleshow/131241650.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-found-fossil-pollen-that-revealed-a-hidden-nile-channel-used-to-build-the-great-pyramid/articleshow/131241650.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:50:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131242180,imgsize-1641937.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Jamsetji Tata: “Uncommon thinkers reuse what common thinkers refuse.”]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131245931.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-jamsetji-tata-uncommon-thinkers-reuse-what-common-thinkers-refuse-/articleshow/131245931.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-jamsetji-tata-uncommon-thinkers-reuse-what-common-thinkers-refuse-/articleshow/131245931.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:00:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131246009,imgsize-86564.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists say this oral spray may finally cure your dog’s nasty breath]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131241694.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Bad dog breath is a common issue for pet owners. Scientists have discovered a new solution in sugarcane molasses. This agricultural waste contains compounds that fight odor-causing bacteria in dogs' mouths. A simple spray made from molasses extract has shown immediate and lasting results. It neutralizes bad smells and reduces harmful bacteria. This natural treatment could revolutionize pet dental care.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-an-unexpected-cure-for-bad-dog-breath/articleshow/131241694.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-an-unexpected-cure-for-bad-dog-breath/articleshow/131241694.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:46:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131242809,imgsize-809525.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How do erasers actually work? It’s more complicated than you think]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131241716.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pencil marks, composed of graphite flakes, adhere to paper fibers through weak van der Waals interactions. Erasers, with a higher affinity for graphite, mechanically lift and trap these flakes while also slightly abrading the paper. Unlike pencil, ink seeps into paper, requiring erasable pens to use heat-activated chemistry to render ink transparent.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-do-erasers-actually-work-its-more-complicated-than-you-think/articleshow/131241716.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-do-erasers-actually-work-its-more-complicated-than-you-think/articleshow/131241716.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:44:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131243152,imgsize-859427.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Oxford AI expert Michael Wooldridge says robot takeover fears miss Big Tech’s real danger]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131241852.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Life's constant negotiations often feel like a rigged game, but Oxford professor Michael Wooldridge argues we can escape the 'zero-sum mindset.' His book, drawing from game theory, reveals most interactions aren't win-or-lose. By understanding strategic thinking, we can foster cooperation, even in AI and business, leading to more fulfilling outcomes for everyone.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/ai-expert-michael-wooldridge-doesnt-worry-about-a-robot-takeover-but-warns-of-big-techs-real-dangers/articleshow/131241852.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/ai-expert-michael-wooldridge-doesnt-worry-about-a-robot-takeover-but-warns-of-big-techs-real-dangers/articleshow/131241852.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:36:25+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131243009,imgsize-487683.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Inside the Belgium-sized wilderness home to Earth’s highest waterfall and monkey-hunting eagles]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131241906.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Venezuela's Canaima National Park offers a journey to a land time forgot, with towering tepuis inspiring 'The Lost World' and 'Up'. These isolated table-top mountains harbor unique ecosystems, acting as living laboratories for evolution. Below, vast savannas teem with giants like jaguars and harpy eagles, while Angel Falls, the world's tallest waterfall, provides a breathtaking spectacle.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/inside-the-belgium-sized-wilderness-home-to-earths-highest-waterfall-and-monkey-hunting-eagles/articleshow/131241906.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/inside-the-belgium-sized-wilderness-home-to-earths-highest-waterfall-and-monkey-hunting-eagles/articleshow/131241906.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T17:35:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131243269,imgsize-1376771.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 2021, a 4-year-old girl walking on a beach spotted a mark in a rock that turned out to be a dinosaur footprint]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131221083.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A remarkable dinosaur footprint, 220 million years old, was found by a young girl in Wales. This trace fossil offers insights into prehistoric life and animal behavior. Scientists are studying the ancient track to understand dinosaur movement. The discovery emphasizes that important finds can be made through simple observation, reminding us of Earth's deep history.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/in-2021-a-4-year-old-girl-walking-on-a-beach-spotted-a-mark-in-a-rock-that-turned-out-to-be-a-dinosaur-footprint/articleshow/131221083.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/in-2021-a-4-year-old-girl-walking-on-a-beach-spotted-a-mark-in-a-rock-that-turned-out-to-be-a-dinosaur-footprint/articleshow/131221083.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T15:59:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131224348,imgsize-244936.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Don't drop it,’ said Prince William as Novak Djokovic handed the 2022 Wimbledon trophy to Prince George]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131221092.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Prince George experienced a memorable moment at Wimbledon's centenary celebration, holding the champion's trophy for the first time. His father, Prince William, humorously warned him not to drop it, leading to a viral family scene. Princess Kate then gently took the trophy, concluding a touching display of royal tradition and childhood learning.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/dont-drop-it-said-prince-william-as-novak-djokovic-handed-the-2022-wimbledon-trophy-to-prince-george/articleshow/131221092.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/dont-drop-it-said-prince-william-as-novak-djokovic-handed-the-2022-wimbledon-trophy-to-prince-george/articleshow/131221092.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-21T16:04:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131240623,imgsize-2025893.cms"/></item></channel></rss>